RIYADH: Saudi Arabia’s Foreign Minister Prince Faisal bin Farhan met with his Egyptian counterpart on the sidelines of a meeting of G20 foreign ministers in New Delhi on Thursday. During the meeting, Prince Faisal and Sameh Shoukry discussed the strong relations and joint cooperation between their countries and aspects of enhancing bilateral work in all fields. The two officials discussed issues of concern, developments on the regional and international arenas, and efforts exerted with regard to them. They also exchanged views on issues on the agenda of the G20 meeting.